Naming Conventions

Use clear, descriptive names. Functions should start with verbs.
Bad: function f() {}
Good: function calculateCustomerAge() {}

Use camelCase for variables/functions.
Bad: $customer_name = "John";
Good: $customerName = "John";

Use PascalCase for class names.
Bad: class customerInfo {}
Good: class CustomerInfo {}

Use full words or well-known acronyms (e.g., enableIdn), avoid abbreviations.

Formatting and Structure
Braces & Indentation: Place opening brace on the same line.

Bad:
if ($condition)
{
    echo "True";
}

Good:
if ($condition) {
    echo "True";
}

Line Length: Keep lines under 80 characters. Break long chains.

Bad:
CustomerInfo::withName("John")->withAge(30)->withCity("NY")->withEmail("x");

Good:
CustomerInfo::withName("John")
    ->withAge(30)
    ->withCity("NY")
    ->withEmail("x");

Blank Lines: Separate logic blocks but don’t overuse.

Bad:
public function getInfo() {

    $info = Get::info();
    if (!$info) {
        throw new Exception();
    }
    return $info;

}

Good:
public function getInfo() {
    $info = Get::info();

    if (!$info) {
        throw new Exception();
        return null;
    }

    return $info;
}

Comments: Write self-explanatory code.

Bad:
// Load info
$info = $this->load($id);

Good:
$paymentInfo = $this->loadPaymentInfoOrCry();

3. Code Organization

Whitespace: Use spaces around operators and after commas.

Bad: if($info){...}
Good: if ($info) { ... }

Method Order: Public methods first, then protected, then private.

Bad:
public function exec() { ... }
private function helper() { ... }

Good:
public function exec() { ... }
private function helper() { ... }

Modularization: Split responsibilities into smaller classes.

Bad:
class ChargeAction {
    public function createRequest() { ... }
    private function createBody() { ... }
}

Good:
class ChargeAction {
    public function createRequest() {
        $httpRequest = new ChargeRequest();
    }
}
class ChargeRequest {
    private function createBody() { ... }
}

4. Best Practices
Always declare method and property visibility (public, private, protected) to ensure encapsulation.
